{"TopicId":119101,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Doors: Now With GPP!","CreatedByName":"Moesly_Armlis","CreatedById":112247,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-23T00:28:20Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Moesly_Armlis","CreatedById":112247,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-23T00:28:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana;\u0022\u003E \u00C3\u00A2\u00E2\u201A\u00AC\u00C5\u201CAll the doors in this spaceship have a cheerful and sunny disposition. It is their pleasure to open for you, and their satisfaction to close again with the knowledge of a job well done.\u00C3\u00A2\u00E2\u201A\u00AC\u00C2 \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana;\u0022\u003EDouglas Adams\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana;\u0022\u003EWhy are kerbals unable to walk out any door and \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana;\u0022\u003EEVA\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana;\u0022\u003E onto the KSC? \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana;\u0022\u003E Currently the only way to have a kerbal go outside is to launch from a vessel.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Verdana;\u0022\u003EAt the very least could the kerbals just exit the doors of the astronaut complex. \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-09-11T04:33:59Z\u0022 title=\u002209/11/2015 04:33  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 11, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by MoeslyArmlis\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Equote\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Whirligig Girl","CreatedById":36077,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-23T01:29:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYou could have phrased this better.. Are you asking for the ability to EVA Kerbals from the astronaut complex for things like rover-transfers to spacecraft? Because that would be cool.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Moesly_Armlis","CreatedById":112247,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-23T01:40:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E@GregroxMun\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFixed. Thanks for re phrasing.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"peachoftree","CreatedById":110108,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-23T02:56:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYes. This would be awesome\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-23T13:57:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENot like it\u0027s really needed, but would be nice to have a spawn option for them there.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stoney3K","CreatedById":139954,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-09-03T14:42:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI think the more simple solution would be just to be able to launch plain Kerbals from either the pad or the runway. That should be very simple to add, since a Kerbal is already a controllable object.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-09-03T15:01:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWhat is GPP in this context?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sam.johnson841","CreatedById":104846,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-09-03T16:03:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EPersonally I would spwan them from the flag pole, close enough to go to swimming in the pool! \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E@RedIronCrown. Gas Planet \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#D3D3D3;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EP\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003Etwo\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E- Sam\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Moesly_Armlis","CreatedById":112247,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-09-11T04:33:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EWhat is GPP in this context?\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe GPP acronym and quote is from Douglas Adams.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.technovelgy.com/ct/content.asp?Bnum=1811\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGenuine People Personalities\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}